F. 150, ll. 83-34. Quia convincitur. . . .facere proposuit. Regular in OB, ΟΟ, OD, OF, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD, ΟΕ, ΟΜ, ΜΕ. Marginal in OA, Y. Omitted in LA. For a discussion of this passage, which in all probability is an omission due to similarity of words in two adjacent lines, see above, p. aar.

F.1sob,ll.1-5. Desudmersis. . . . poterit. Regular in OB, OF, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD, ΟΜ, ME, ΟΕ. Inserted aster confiscentur, l. 00, f. 150, in OC; alter haberet, l. 35, f. 150, in OD. Marginal in OA, Y. Omitted in LA, OG. Inasmuch as in all the manuscripts examined this additio is omitted only in those which regularly omit the additional passages in this portion of their text, it must be ascribed to Bracton.

F. 151, l. 66. Per ancilium curioe et per breve. Regular in OA, MD, ME. Omitted in OB, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, LA, ΟΕ, CM, Y, and therefore of doubtful authorship.

Fs.151-151b,ll.aa-a. Siquisvero. . . . periculo crit. Regular in OB, MA, ΜΒ, MD, ME, ΟΕ, ΟΜ, Β (marks as additional). Marginal in Y. Omitted in LA. MC omits only the last sentence in sect. 5. OA inserts as aseparate paragraph aster conductio, l. 8, f. l5lb. Seemingly from Bracton.

F. 152, ll. 8-12. Elqui . . . .iudicatrts. Regular in OF, MH. Inserted aster oblatraverit, l. 7, in ME; aster condemnabitur, l. 10, in OC, MD. Marginal in OA, LC, W. Omitted in OB, OD, MA, MB, MC, LA, ΟΕ, ΟΜ. Of doubtful authorship.

Fs.155b156,ll.88-5. Et eodem naodo. . . . estiterit. Regular in OF, OC, OD, MC, MD, MH, ME, LD. In B this passage is marked as two addicimaes, the second coming aster dedraquit, l. 10, Ι. 156; ME is similar to B inthis respect. Marginal in OA, LA. Omitted in OB, MA, ΜΒ, MI, LC, ΟΕ, ΟΜ. As this additio is supported by (ΙΙ) ÷ (ΙΙΙ) it is presumably from Bracton.

F. 156, ΙΙ. 16-19. Sicca pro damno. . . .vel entra. Regular in OA, OB, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD, ΟΕ, ΟΜ. Inserted aster concedat, l. 25, in LD, ME, Β (marks additional). Marginal in LA. Clearly from Bracton.
